7ï¸âƒ£ substring() â€” Overloaded Methods
ğŸ‘‰ Definition: Extracts a portion (subpart) of a string.
                                  ğŸ”¸ (1) substring(int beginIndex)
                                         Returns substring from given index to end.
                                         "Hello".substring(2);  // "llo"
                                  ğŸ”¸ (2) substring(int beginIndex, int endIndex)
                                         Returns substring between two indexes (endIndex is exclusive).
                                         "Hello".substring(1, 4);  // "ell"

8ï¸âƒ£ split(String regex)
ğŸ‘‰ Definition: Splits a string into parts using a pattern (regex) and returns an array.
